glosses: to rip out; to take out; to take down

examples.translation: The wind ripped the tree out of ground.

glosses: to dismantle, take apart; to rip, undo, unstitch; to unravel
to overcome, get through or over (a place difficult of passage), outgo

examples.text: Araba çamuru sökemedi gemi akıntıyı söktü.
examples.translation: The car couldn't get out of the mud, but the ship got through the current.

glosses: to decipher (handwriting); to understand, get the meaning of (an abstruse passage)
to learn to read (an alphabet); to learn (to read)
(for a drug) to cause (mucus, urine, feces) to be discharged
to make a dent on (someone), affect (someone)

etymology: From Ottoman Turkish سوكمك (sökmek), from Proto-Turkic *sök- (“to split, tear apart”).
